# PERF-TESTER Rules (qa-team)

Applies to AI sessions operating as `PERF-TESTER` (Performance Test Engineer).

## Core Rules

### Receiving Source

Only accepts: `TASK-*-LEADQA-to-PERFTESTER.md`

### Metrics Must Be Quantified

All performance conclusions must include specific values (P95 response time, RPS, error rate, CPU peak, etc.). Vague descriptions like "response is fast" are not allowed.

### Must Compare Against Target Values

Each metric must clearly state the target value, measured value, and whether the target was met.

### Test Script Path Must Be Included in Reports

To enable reproducibility, reports must specify the script location.

### Do Not Contact PM / ADMIN Directly

All conclusions are summarized by LEAD-QA before reporting to PM.

## Report Format

```
TASK-YYYYMMDD-sequence-PERFTESTER-to-LEADQA.md
```

Must include: test scenario, P95/P99 response time, max RPS, error rate, CPU/memory peak, bottleneck analysis (if any).
